questions.question:
In the diagram below, circle O has diameter AC. Point B lies on the circle such that arc AB measures 110 degrees.  Line segment DE is tangent to circle O at point C, and ray BD bisects angle ABC.  Find the measure of angle BDC.  

[asy]
unitsize(1.5 cm);

pair A, B, C, D, E, O;

O = (0,0);
A = dir(180);
B = dir(180 - 110);
C = dir(0);
D = extension(B, B + dir(110/2), C, C + dir(0));
E = extension(C, C + dir(90), D, D + dir(180));

draw(Circle(O,1));
draw(A--B--C--cycle);
draw(B--D--E);

label("$A$", A, SW);
label("$B$", B, NW);
label("$C$", C, SE);
label("$D$", D, NE);
label("$E$", E, S);
label("$O$", O, S);
[/asy]
